CHOLERA - ARMENIA (02)
**********************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Cholera - Armenia 980907230923
Date: Wed, 9 Sep 1998 16:24:57 -0400
Source: Armenian news agency Snark, 9 Jul 1998 & media sources
Via: GPHIN

Three people have died and more than 200 have been hospitalized as a result
of a cholera epidemic, Snark news agency has learned from well-informed
sources.
As has already been reported, cholera bacteria was detected on 3rd and 4th
September in the village of Zartonk of Armenia's Armavir Region. Reports
say that some families from this village left their homes and moved to
other districts of the republic. There is reliable information that one of
the families has settled in Stepanavan (Lori Region) and that a woman from
this family has been hospitalized with suspected cholera. Seventeen people
are in the Nork children's isolation clinic in Yerevan, including children
under the age of 14. The diagnosis of cholera has been confirmed in four of
the hospitalized people, it has not been confirmed in two cases and the
other 11 have been in contact with infected people.
Manvel Manrikyan, main state physician of the republic and Artavazd Vanyan,
head of the hygiene and epidemics supervision are in the village of
Zartonk, the seat of infection.
